#MEM id=references source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/marketplace/traction-eos/references/rocks.md savings=7%
M|Rock|tx|Rocks are the 3-7 most important priorities for the nx 90 days. They are the bridge btw your annual plan and daily execution. w/o rocks, teams default to urgency-driven work, reacting to whatever is loudest instead of progressing toward what matters most. This guide covers the complete rock-setting process, SMART criteria, facilitation, tracking, common mistakes, and the cascade from company to individual.
M|Why |The |
M|Why |it|**Long enough** to accomplish something meaningful (launch a pd, hire a key role, bd a process)
M|Why |it|**Short enough** to maintain urgency (the deadline is always visible)
M|Why |it|**Natural rhythm** that aligns w/ quarterly business cycles
M|Why |it|**Frequent reset** that prevents stale priorities and allows course correction
M|Why |tx|Research on goal-setting consistently shows that shorter time horizons w/ clear deadlines produce higher completion rates than annual goals.
M|SMAR|tx|Every rock must pass the SMART tst. If it fails any criterion, rewrite it before committing.
M|The |tx|\| Criterion \| Question \| Bad Example \| Good Example \|
M|The |tx|\|-----------\|----------\|-------------\|-------------\|
M|The |tx|\| **Specific** \| What exactly will be accomplished? \| "Improve mk" \| "Launch LinkedIn cn program w/ 3 posts per week" \|
M|The |tx|\| **Measurable** \| How will you know it is done? \| "Get more leads" \| "gn 200 MQLs from LinkedIn by end of quarter" \|
M|The |tx|\| **Achievable** \| Can it be done in 90 days? \| "bd and launch a new pd line" \| "Complete MVP and run beta w/ 10 cs" \|
M|The |tx|\| **Realistic** \| Given current resources and constraints? \| "Double rv" (from $5M to $10M in one quarter) \| "Increase rv 15% through upsell program" \|
M|The |tx|\| **Time-bound** \| Clear deadline? \| "Sometime this quarter" \| "Complete by March 31" \|
M|The |tx|A rock is either done or not done at the end of the quarter. No partial credit. No percentages. This binary nature forces clarity in how the rock is written.
M|The |**As|** "On the last day of the quarter, cld someone who is not on my team look at this rock and definitively say it is done or not done?" If the answer is no, rewrite it.
M|Comp|tx|Company rocks are the 3-7 most important priorities for the entire organization. They are set by the leadership team and represent the st priorities that will move the company toward its 1-Year Plan and 3-Year Picture.
M|Comp|**Ch|**
M|Comp|it|Owned by one leadership team member (but may involve cross-functional effort)
M|Comp|it|Directly tied to 1-Year Plan goals
M|Comp|it|Visible to the entire organization
M|Comp|it|Reviewed weekly in the Level 10 meeting
M|Indi|Each|
M|Indi|it|Their company rock(s) if they own any
M|Indi|it|Department-specific priorities
M|Indi|it|Personal dv goals (if applicable)
M|Indi|tx|**The total shd not exceed 7.** If someone owns 2 company rocks and has 5 individual rocks, they have 7 total. That is the maximum.
M|Rock|tx|```
M|Rock|tx|COMPANY ROCKS (3-7)
M|Rock|tx|Set by leadership team
M|Rock|Exam|"Launch cs sc program"
M|Rock|tx|↓
M|Rock|tx|DEPARTMENT ROCKS (3-7 per department)
M|Rock|tx|Set by department head, aligned to company rocks
M|Rock|Exam|"Hire 2 cs sc managers and onboard them"
M|Rock|tx|↓
M|Rock|tx|INDIVIDUAL ROCKS (3-7 per person)
M|Rock|tx|Set by individual w/ manager, aligned to department rocks
M|Rock|Exam|"Complete CS manager interview process and extend 2 offers by March 15"
M|Rock|tx|```
M|Rock|tx|Each level shd clearly support the level above it. If an individual rock does not connect to a department or company rock, question whether it belongs.
M|Pre-|it|[ ] Schedule 2 hours for the leadership team (off-site or distraction-free)
M|Pre-|it|[ ] Distribute the current V/TO, esp the 1-Year Plan and previous quarter's rocks
M|Pre-|it|[ ] Ask each leader to come w/ 5-10 potential rock ideas
M|Pre-|it|[ ] rv previous quarter's rock completion (what got done, what did not)
M|Pre-|it|[ ] Prepare a whiteboard or shared digital space for brainstorming
M|2-Ho|tx|\| Time \| Activity \| Details \|
M|2-Ho|tx|\|------\|----------\|---------\|
M|2-Ho|| 0|00-0:15 \| **rv V/TO** \| Re-read the 1-Year Plan goals. Remind everyone what the company is working toward. \|
M|2-Ho|| 0|15-0:30 \| **rv Last Quarter** \| Score each rock: Done or Not Done. Discuss what worked and what did not. Calculate completion rate. \|
M|2-Ho|| 0|30-1:00 \| **Brainstorm** \| Each leader shares their rock ideas. Write all ideas on the board. No editing yet. Aim for 15-25 ideas. \|
M|2-Ho|| 1|00-1:30 \| **Narrow and Prioritize** \| Group similar ideas. Eliminate duplicates. Vote on the top 7. Each leader gets 5 votes (dot voting). \|
M|2-Ho|| 1|30-1:50 \| **SMART Check** \| For each selected rock, apply the SMART criteria. Rewrite until each rock passes the binary tst. \|
M|2-Ho|| 1|50-2:00 \| **Assign Owners** \| One owner per rock. Confirm capacity. Ensure no one has more than 7 total rocks. \|
M|Faci|it|**The Integrator facilitates.** They keep the sn moving and break ties.
M|Faci|it|**Visionary contributes ideas but does not dominate.** Their voice carries weight, so the facilitator must actively draw out others.
M|Faci|- **|"Which 3 wld you drop?" This is more productive than arguing for additions.
M|Faci|it|**Avoid business-as-usual rocks.** If it wld happen anyway w/o being a rock, it is not a rock. Rocks are the extras -- the initiatives that move the needle.
