M|Rock|tx|Rocks are reviewed every week in the Level 10 meeting. The rv takes 5 minutes and follows a simple protocol.
M|Week|tx|1. **Display the rock sheet** showing all company and individual rocks
M|Week|2. *|"On track" or "Off track."
M|Week|tx|3. **No discussion during rv.** Off-track rocks are noted.
M|Week|tx|4. **Off-track rocks drop to Issues List.** They will be IDS'd during the 60-minute IDS portion of the meeting.
M|Week|5. *|5 minutes.** This is a status scan, not a progress rp.
M|Rock|tx|\| Rock \| Owner \| Status W1 \| W2 \| W3 \| W4 \| W5 \| W6 \| W7 \| W8 \| W9 \| W10 \| W11 \| W12 \| W13 \| Done? \|
M|Rock|tx|\|------\|-------\|-----------\|----\|----\|----\|----\|----\|----\|----\|----\|-----\|-----\|-----\|-----\|-----\|-------\|
M|Rock|tx|\| Launch partner channel \| Sarah \| On \| On \| On \| Off \| On \| On \| On \| On \| On \| On \| On \| On \| On \| Yes \|
M|Rock|tx|\| Hire VP Sales \| James \| On \| On \| Off \| Off \| On \| On \| On \| On \| On \| On \| On \| On \| On \| Yes \|
M|Rock|tx|\| Ship v2.0 \| Priya \| On \| On \| On \| On \| On \| On \| Off \| Off \| Off \| On \| On \| On \| On \| No \|
M|The |tx|The goal is to complete 80% or more of rocks each quarter. This is a team metric, not an individual one.
M|What|tx|\| Rate \| Interpretation \| Action \|
M|What|tx|\|------\|---------------\|--------\|
M|What|tx|\| **90-100%** \| Rocks may be too easy \| Set more ambitious rocks nx quarter \|
M|What|tx|\| **80-89%** \| Healthy execution \| Maintain the bar and celebrate \|
M|What|| **|too many rocks? Wrong rocks? Resource constraints? \|
M|What|| **|capacity, commitment, or rock qual \|
M|Impr|If t|
M|Impr|it|[ ] Were rocks written clearly (SMART)? If not, improve rock-writing discipline
M|Impr|it|[ ] Were there too many rocks? If yes, reduce to 3-5 nx quarter
M|Impr|it|[ ] Did priorities shift mid-quarter? If yes, the team needs better discipline around saying no to new priorities
M|Impr|it|[ ] Did one person miss all their rocks? If yes, it is a people issue (capacity or commitment)
M|Impr|it|[ ] Did the whole team miss? If yes, it may be an organizational capacity issue
M|Comm|tx|\| Mistake \| Why It Fails \| Fix \|
M|Comm|tx|\|---------\|-------------\|-----\|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Too many rocks (>7)** \| Diluted focus, everything moves slowly \| Force the team to choose. Fewer rocks, more done. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Too vague** \| Cannot tell if it is done at quarter end \| Apply the binary tst. Rewrite until it passes. \|
M|Comm|| **|"wld this happen even if it were not a rock?" If yes, it is not a rock. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **No owner** \| Shared accountability is no accountability \| One name per rock. Period. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Rock is really a to-do** \| Too small for a 90-day priority \| If it can be done in a week, put it on the to-do list, not the rock sheet. \|
M|Comm|| **|"Launch upsell program targeting top 50 accounts" \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Changing rocks mid-quarter** \| Destroys the 90-day discipline \| Rocks are locked once set. New ur items become to-dos or wait for nx quarter. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Not tracking weekly** \| Out of sight, out of mind \| rv every rock in every Level 10 meeting \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **No consequences for missed rocks** \| Team learns that rocks are optional \| IDS missed rocks. Identify why. Address the pattern. \|
M|Mid-|At t|
M|Mid-|1. *|** Each owner rates their rocks as on track, at risk, or off track
M|Mid-|2. *|** For each at-risk rock, discuss:
M|Mid-|it|What is blocking progress?
M|Mid-|it|What support is needed?
M|Mid-|it|Is the rock still achievable by end of quarter?
M|Mid-|it|If not, shd we adjust scope or accept the miss?
M|Mid-|3. *|** Each person states what they will do in the nx 6 weeks to complete their rocks
M|Mid-|tx|```
M|Mid-|Rock|
M|Mid-|tx|├── On track → Continue, no action needed
M|Mid-|tx|├── At risk → IDS the obstacle, get support, recommit
M|Mid-|└── |
M|Mid-|tx|├── 1. Recommit w/ adjusted approach (still achievable)
M|Mid-|tx|├── 2. Reduce scope to core deliverable (partial but meaningful)
M|Mid-|tx|└── 3. Accept the miss and learn from it (do not carry forward automatically)
M|Mid-|tx|```
M|Mid-|**Im|** Do not add new rocks mid-quarter. The 90-day discipline requires that priorities stay locked. If something truly ur arises, it becomes a to-do, not a rock.
